TEXT -648 256 Left 2 !.tran 0 100m 10u startup
TEXT 1384 -224 Left 2 ;changing value of either R or C changes the period of the oscillations\nfreq = 1 / 2RCV\nchanging the value of C has a much more dramatic effect than changing the value of R\ndecreasing value of C seems to make the sawtooth effect more dramatic\n \nthe diodes make the "sawtooth" shape, they make the positive slope steeper.\nthe fewer diodes there are in series, the steeper this slope becomes.\n \nRa forms a high-pass filter (probably) with C \nRemember that R and C also form a low-pass filter, so be mindful when editing their values\nRa=100k, frequencies above 5kHz are cut off\nRa=100, frequencies above 200Hz are cut off\nRa=10k, fairly even distribution of frequencies, slight dB drop off for freq above 1kHz\n \nR1, R2 and R6, R7 form voltage dividers that control the amplitude of both waveforms\nediting the voltage dividers of one oscillator affects the amplitude of the other oscillators waveform
TEXT -648 296 Left 2 !.param R=10k
TEXT -648 328 Left 2 !.param C=10n
TEXT -648 368 Left 2 !.param Ra=8.2k
TEXT -984 256 Left 2 ;---Original Values---\nR1 = 8.2k
TEXT -352 256 Left 2 ;.ac dec 1000 20Hz 20kHz
TEXT 728 488 Left 2 ;R6 = 2.2k\nR7 = 10k
